messages.content: I want to buy a MacBook, but it's too expensive. I remember using a large discount on a previous order. Could you compare that old discount with my current one? If the previous one was better, please refund that order and apply the refunded discount to this MacBook purchase to make it as cheap as possible.

<function_thought>
The user wants to purchase a MacBook and is concerned about the price. They recall using a large discount on a previous order and want to compare that with their current available discounts. If the previous discount was better, they want that order refunded so the discount can be reused on the MacBook purchase.

The first step in the trajectory is to view the order history to identify past orders where a significant discount might have been used. This will allow us to select a candidate order for further investigation.
</function_thought>

<function_call>[view_order_history()]</function_call>
